title: For Sale:  S&W 629-6 .44mag. Stainless 4" Mountain Gun with S&W Wood Presentation Case, and Two Sets of Grips
postcontent: S&W 629-6 .44mag. Stainless 4" Mountain Gun with S&W Wood Presentation Case, a set of Pachmyr Grips, & a set of Altamont Silverblack Combat Grips. Shes a beautiful collector wheel gun with only minor fading to laser etched areas. She is 1 of 1000 that were made during the 3rd and last run of the 629 Mountain Gun.The 629 Mountain Gun was a limited run/edition revolver that was also done for the model 29. They were produced to be a "lightweight" backcountry carry gun. There were only 3 production runs of it between 1989 to 2005, making them sought after by collectors. Total production number for both models was 15000 with 6 dashes/changes on the 629 during the timeframe of production. My 629-6 Mountain Gun was in the 3rd and last production run. There were only 1000 629's produced during that run. The Mountain Gun had square butts until dash 4, then went to round butts. It came with a tapered 4" Barrel that was 2ozs lighter than the 629 Classic. Mountain gun also had beveled/curved areas around the end of the cylinder for smoother placement of the revolver back into a holster. The MG had a smooth textured trigger, whereas the Classic had the target style serrations texture. MG maintained wide hammer. MG front sight post was all black, as well as rear adj. sight post. The classic had red front sight post with white outlined rear post. The dash-6 came with the lock. $950 cash, or $1100 cash and/or trade. CWP preferred, but SCDL with no felonies will be required.
